          <img src=@{StaticR tom_sydney_kerckhove_coding_experience_svg} alt="coding experience" style="height: 400px">

        <div .column>
          <p .title .is-size-4>
            No coding experience needed

          <p .content .is-normal .has-text-justified>
            But it does help.
            Because of its optimization for speed Smos is a command line interface tool.            
            If you buy the 
            <a href=https://cs-syd.eu/self-management target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              self-management coaching
            you get detailed instructions of Smos' features if desired (installation, commands, reasoning, modifiability).
            We have also published the
            <a href=https://docs.smos.online/ target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              documentation of Smos
            as well as a
            <a href=https://smos.online/tui/example.smos target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              browser version of Smos          
            and a
            <a href=https://docs.smos.online/cheat-sheet target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              cheat sheet
            with the most important commands, which should help to speed up the learning process.



    <section .section>
      <div .columns .is-vcentered>
        <div .column>
          <p .title .is-size-4 .has-text-right>
            Psychological bliss

          <p .content .is-normal .has-text-justified>  
            Smos is centered around the idea of combining all psychological healthy ways of working so you know exactly what it is that you need to do.            
            Just to name a few: the feeling of satisfaction when you have finished a task, being able to evade procrastination by knowing exactly what your next small action is, and having a smart overview of all your projects.

        <div .column .has-text-centered>
          <img src=@{StaticR tom_sydney_kerckhove_mental_health_svg} alt="psychological bliss" style="height: 400px">



    <section .section>
